<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,253,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,325,350]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is a compound noun from the indigenous language Tupi, roughly meaning “similar people”, from which the name of the state of Goiás is derived.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,253,926]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,397,422]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[438,603,398,421]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Xiruana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guaia" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[438,603,398,421]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Xiruana guaia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[611,675,397,422]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[611,626,397,422]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">n</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[642,668,397,422]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are promptly recognized by the median apophysis strongly curved medially, forming a bend with more than 
<number box="[615,643,433,457]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="90.0">90</number>
degree, and by the short median tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1289,433,458]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1780]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Xiruana guaia n. sp.: A male left palp, ventral view; B same, retrolateral view (arrow: basal projection of median apophysis); C same, median apophysis; D male palpal tibia, retrolateral view; E same, retrodorsal view; F same, dorsal view. Xiruana affinis (Mello-Leitão): G female epigynum, ventral view; H same, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, B 0.5 mm; C 0.1 mm; H 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242240/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number box="[1264,1289,433,457]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
A–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
